# Streaming Chat Completions

Streaming delivers generated tokens incrementally via Server-Sent Events (SSE). Instead of waiting for the entire response, you receive each token as the model produces it.

## Basic Streaming

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI();

const stream = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [
    { role: "system", content: "You are a helpful assistant." },
    { role: "user", content: "Write a short poem about programming." },
  ],
  stream: true,
});

for await (const chunk of stream) {
  const content = chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content || "";
  process.stdout.write(content);
}
console.log(); // newline after stream ends
```

## With Usage Tracking

To get token usage with streaming, set `stream_options.include_usage`:

```javascript
const stream = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [{ role: "user", content: "Hello!" }],
  stream: true,
  stream_options: { include_usage: true },
});

let usage = null;
for await (const chunk of stream) {
  const content = chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content || "";
  process.stdout.write(content);
  if (chunk.usage) {
    usage = chunk.usage;
  }
}

console.log(`\nTokens: ${usage.prompt_tokens} prompt + ${usage.completion_tokens} completion = ${usage.total_tokens} total`);
```

## Collecting Full Response

Accumulate chunks when you need both streaming output and the full text:

```javascript
const chunks = [];
for await (const chunk of stream) {
  const content = chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content || "";
  chunks.push(content);
  process.stdout.write(content);
}
const fullResponse = chunks.join("");
```

## SSE Wire Format

The raw HTTP response is a series of `data:` lines. Each line contains a JSON chunk:

```
data: {"id":"chatcmpl-abc","choices":[{"index":0,"delta":{"role":"assistant"},"finish_reason":null}]}

data: {"id":"chatcmpl-abc","choices":[{"index":0,"delta":{"content":"Hello"},"finish_reason":null}]}

data: {"id":"chatcmpl-abc","choices":[{"index":0,"delta":{"content":"!"},"finish_reason":null}]}

data: {"id":"chatcmpl-abc","choices":[{"index":0,"delta":{},"finish_reason":"stop"}]}

data: [DONE]
```

## cURL Streaming

```bash
curl -N https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $OPENAI_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "model": "gpt-4o",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello!"}],
    "stream": true
  }'
```

## Abort / Cancel

Use an AbortController to cancel a stream mid-generation:

```javascript
const controller = new AbortController();

const stream = await client.chat.completions.create(
  {
    model: "gpt-4o",
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: "Write a long essay." }],
    stream: true,
  },
  { signal: controller.signal },
);

setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 5000); // cancel after 5s

try {
  for await (const chunk of stream) {
    process.stdout.write(chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content || "");
  }
} catch (err) {
  if (err.name === "AbortError") {
    console.log("\nStream cancelled.");
  } else {
    throw err;
  }
}
```

